<unittitle>All On Together [Government Receiving Home}</unittitle>
<unitdate>18 August 1935</unitdate>
<abstract>This is a picture from the <span style="font-style:italic">Sunday Times</span> newspaper, which is published on the National Library of Australia's website, 'Trove'. It shows a group of children on a see-saw in the playground of the Government Receiving Home in Walcott Street, Mt Lawley in 1935. This image was one of several pictures of the Home, illustrating a newspaper article ('Where the Little Wards of the State are Drafted').</abstract>
